    <item>
      <title>Domestic Horticulturalists</title>
      <link>https://apophenian.art/poetry/domestic-horticulturalists/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://apophenian.art/poetry/domestic-horticulturalists/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The grass has grown so long,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;It is underfoot no more.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;It is around our ankles,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Our knees,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Our eyes.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;A green jungle,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;The blue sky.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;A tiger like kitten&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Prowls the grasslands and prairies of our love.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;A rumbling purr,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;A quiet resentment,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;A long past feeling of order and restraint.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;A painful clarity and of course,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;The hopeless boredom&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Of you&lt;br&gt;&#xA;And me&lt;br&gt;&#xA;And our contempt for gardening.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
